docs.abstract: Workers at tech companies like Amazon are starting to use the stock grants that they were paid to turn the tables on their employers.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Silicon Valley technology firms are known for giving stock to their workers, a form of compensation that often helps employees feel invested in their companies.

docs.abstract: Legal challenges forced the agency to scrap bids for a new website and other tech changes aimed at simplifying the repayment process for millions of borrowers.
docs.snippet: Legal challenges forced the agency to scrap bids for a new website and other tech changes aimed at simplifying the repayment process for millions of borrowers.
docs.lead_paragraph: Just seven months before the scheduled release of a new technology system intended to simplify the repayment process for more than 35 million federal student loan borrowers, the Education Department is scrapping its plan and starting over.

headline.main: Education Dept. Cancels Plan for New Student Loan System and Will Try Again
headline.print_headline: Education Dept. Resets Plan To Overhaul Its Loan System

docs.abstract: Car sales are falling. Housing is slow. Workers get three-month unpaid vacations. For Chinese leaders, pressure for a trade deal with President Trump is rising.
docs.snippet: Car sales are falling. Housing is slow. Workers get three-month unpaid vacations. For Chinese leaders, pressure for a trade deal with President Trump is rising.
docs.lead_paragraph: DONGGUAN, China — China’s consumers and businesses are losing confidence. Car sales have plunged. The housing market is stumbling. Some factories are letting workers off for the big Lunar New Year holiday two months early.

headline.main: China’s Economy Slows Sharply, in Challenge for Xi Jinping

byline.original: By Keith Bradsher and Ailin Tang

docs.abstract: The companies say their new venture will be the world’s largest maker of over-the-counter products like pain relievers, toothpastes, cold treatments, vitamins and dietary supplements.

headline.main: GlaxoSmithKline and Pfizer to Merge Consumer Health Units

docs.abstract: Only 20 miles of Maine’s 3,500-mile shoreline is considered working waterfront, and residents are grappling with whether to preserve it or reshape it.
docs.snippet: Only 20 miles of Maine’s 3,500-mile shoreline is considered working waterfront, and residents are grappling with whether to preserve it or reshape it.
docs.lead_paragraph: BOOTHBAY HARBOR, Me. — As a child, Paul Coulombe used to spend lazy summer days with his family in this tiny coastal village. Now, convinced the town “hasn’t kept up,” he has plans to reshape it.

headline.main: Maine Waterfront Quandary: Restoration or Redevelopment?
